POSTAL MUTUAL BENEFIT CORPORATION, Appellant, v. Jane B. FROST, Appellee. No. 7674. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Oct. 7, 1937. John H. McNeal and Harley J. Mc-Neal, both of Cleveland, Ohio, for appellant. Pollack & Pollack, of Cleveland, Ohio, for appellee.

Before HICKS, SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered, pursuant to stipulation of counsel, that the appeal herein be, and the same is, dismissed at the costs of appellant.
